It is clear that volcanoes are located along the edges of the tectonic plates.

What are those straight lines that are occurring? Perhaps some volcanoes are repeatedly erupting? Lets have a look.

count_of_counts %>% 
ggplot(aes(x=e_count, y= no_volc)) + 
    geom_point(size=1, colour ="firebrick") +
    labs(
      x = "Number of times a volcano has erupted",
      y = "Count of Volcanoes",
      title = "How many times does a volcano erupt?"
      )

The majority of volcanoes erupt rarely (from what we know) - 27% have only erupted once - 72% 10 or fewer eruptions - 83% 20 or fewer - 95% 50 or fewer

But there are some volcanoes that we know erupt a lot. 8 of the volcanoes have known to have erupted at least 100 times.
